sizes others are made up with layers of mesh and felt, some use membrane type
materials.
Magnetic filters (Figure 4.27) provide extra protection for engines and
gearboxes where iron or steel wear particles are likely to be present.
Further reading
Milton, J. H. and Leach, R. M. (1980) Marine Steam Boilers, 4th edn. Butterworths.
